<section id="colorBlock" class="hero is-fullheight" >
  <h1 class="title" style="padding-top: 15px;">
    {{ brandName }}'s Color
  </h1>

  <h2 class="subtitle container">
    All colors have inherent meanings, which can vary depending on the country or culture. These meanings have a direct impact on the way your visitors perceive your site, even if it’s just subconsciously. The colors you choose can either work for or against the brand identity you’re trying to create. One of the easiest color schemes to create. By adding a bright accent color into an otherwise-neutral palette, you can easily create an effective  color scheme.
  </h2>  

  <h2 style="color:{{chosenPrimary}}; font-size: 18px;">Primary color: {{chosenName}}</h2>

  <h2 style="color:{{chosenComplimentary}};font-size: 18px"> Complimentary color: {{complimentaryName}}</h2> 

<div class="hero-content" > 
<h2 class="subtitle" style="font-size: 20px; color: {{textColor}}">
    {{ colorInfo }}
  </h2>   
<div class="container is-fluid">
  
<div class="columns">

  <div class="column" ng-repeat="color in colorPallate">
    <div class="circleBase" ng-mouseenter="$parent.colorInfo = color.info" ng-click="$parent.chosenPrimary = color.color; $parent.chosenName = color.name; $parent.complimentaryName = color.compName; $parent.chosenComplimentary = color.compColor" style="background:{{color.color}};" >
    <p class="hero-content" > {{color.name}}</p>
      </div>    
  </div>
    

</div>      
</div>
</div>
  <i id="colorScroll" style="margin-bottom: 15px;"class="fa fa-chevron-down fa-5x whiteScroller"></i>
</section>